# Substrate Project Rules (The Constitution)

## Project File Map (Read before any task)
- `DESIGN.md` — Complete technical blueprint.
- `schema.ts` — Zod schemas for BusinessNode, BusinessEdge, Modifier, Experience.
- `events.ts` — Event type literals (NODE_CREATED, EDGE_ADDED, MODIFIER_ATTACHED, etc.).
- `store.ts` — Zustand CanvasStore (dispatch, undo/redo, command stack).
- `adapters/reactFlowAdapter.ts` — Business data -> React Flow format.
- `db.ts` — Dexie.js setup (topics, events, snapshots).
- `supabase.ts` — Supabase client and sync.
- `shortcuts.ts` — All keyboard shortcuts as constants.

## Technical Stack & Constraints
- Framework: React (Latest), TypeScript, Tailwind CSS.
- Canvas: React Flow (v12+).
- State: Zustand (no Immer, immutable spreads).
- Validation: Zod (Migration on Read — all persistent data parsed on load).
- DB: Supabase (PostgreSQL JSONB) + IndexedDB (Dexie.js).
- Architecture: ECS-inspired, composition over inheritance.

## Data Model Invariants
- 4 entity types: Node, Edge, Modifier, Experience.
- Node types: 'component' | 'goal'. (Experience is NOT a node type.)
- Edge types: 'flat' | 'directed_thought'.
- Modifier types: 'text', 'image', 'scope', 'syntax'. Always attached to a Node or Edge.
- Experience: standalone, has `targets: {id, type}[]`, one-time mapping (no physics binding).

## Engineering Taboos (Absolute No-Go)
- NO Static Singletons.
- NO Deep Inheritance.
- NO Silent Failures (fail loudly with Zod or assertions).
- NO Magic Strings — use Enums/Literals from `events.ts` and `schema.ts`.
- NO Side Effects in Reducers — all state changes pure, logging/sync in dispatch coordinator.
- NO Unmemoized Custom React Flow Nodes — always wrap with `React.memo`.

## Data Flow Rules
- Single Source of Truth: Zustand `CanvasStore` (business nodes, edges, experiences).
- Append-only Event Stream: Every state change writes an event to IndexedDB `events` table.
- View-Model Separation: Business data != React Flow data. Use `reactFlowAdapter.ts`.
- Move Performance: `NODE_MOVED` event ONLY on `onNodeDragStop`. No events during drag.
- Sync: Local-first, then push to Supabase (LWW per topic). Load snapshot first, then replay events.
- Undo/Redo: Command stack (max 50) + mark UNDO/REDO events in stream. No physical deletion.

## UI & Interaction Rules
- Right-click: Flat hierarchy. [New Component] [New Goal] [Paste] on top.
- Shortcuts: Loaded from `shortcuts.ts`. Defaults: C (Component), G (Goal), S (Thought mode), L (Lasso), Esc (default mode).
- Lasso: Select nodes/edges, create Experience with `targets` snapshot. No dynamic binding after creation.
- Nodes >200 in one canvas: show warning, suggest splitting topic.

## Prompting Instructions for AI
- Always reference `@DESIGN.md` and `@schema.ts` when implementing data logic.
- Before writing complex logic, describe the plan in markdown first (unless tests already provided).
- If a modification fails twice, restart in a new Chat thread with clean context.